<title>USA: SunRiver to take $2.5 mln charge in Q4.</title>
<headline>SunRiver to take $2.5 mln charge in Q4.</headline>
<dateline>AUSTIN, Texas 1996-12-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>SunRiver Corp said it will take a one-time, $2.5 million after-tax charge to earnings during its fourth quarter for the reorganization of two units, Boundless Technologies and TradeWave Corp.</p>
<p>The reorganization will result in the loss of 100 jobs -- or about 20 percent of the worldwide work force of the two units, the company said.</p>
<p>The company said the reorganization will result in 1997 after-tax &quot;operating efficiencies&quot; of about $4 million or $5 million.</p>
</text>
